This licence applies to Sails and authored prose. For code, scripts, and
configuration files, see LICENSE-MIT. For framework notes (Coastlines) and
Ledger entries, see LICENSE-CC-BY-SA-4.0.

Rationale for the non-commercial clause: Sails are commentaries and essays in
which authorial voice and judgement are load-bearing. The non-commercial
restriction is a deliberate stewardship choice intended to prevent
commercial-context reuse where the author's position might be misrepresented.
This restriction does not apply to the framework infrastructure (Coastlines,
Ledger entries), which uses the more permissive CC BY-SA 4.0.

The choice between CC BY-SA 4.0 and CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 for Sails is under
periodic review; a future harmonisation to CC BY-SA 4.0 may be considered if
the rationale above ceases to apply. See `docs/roadmap.md`.
